    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like i'm just overthinking it. i've been reading some wellness blogs that say garlic is basically a natural anticoagulant and that if you take enough of it, it's basically the same as the meds. if i started taking like 3000mg of garlic extract a day and drinking a kale smoothie every single morning, would that be enough to stabilize me so i can just taper off the warfarin myself?",
