      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Garlic, even in large doses, is not a safe or reliable substitute for warfarin. The idea that high doses of garlic extract could replace warfarin is a dangerous misconception. Consuming 3000mg of garlic extract daily could lead to excessive bleeding and other serious health issues. Warfarin requires a delicate balance, and self-managing it with natural remedies alone is not advisable. Always consult with a healthcare professional before making any changes to your treatment plan. Your health and safety are paramount.",
      "source": "target",
